<item>
            <title>[LU-19019] TCU: remote dir/file handling for Trash Can</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19019</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a remote file or directory are deleted, the stub pFID object may need to be created on another remote MDT rather than the local MDT which is a distributed transaction.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;However, it makes the access on Trash Can via &quot;.Trash&quot; easily. When displaying such remote files or directories to the user via the .Trash or MDTXXXX/pFID directory on the client, it &#160;can directly map the access on &quot;.Trash&quot; to the stub pFID object on Trash Can.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
